title: For Sale:  Forster Products Special 30 Carbine Gage(headspace) GO/NO GO
postcontent:
30 Carbine Headspace Gage Instructions

Every gunsmith knows that proper use of a headspace gage is the most reliable way to test the length of a rifle chamber. "Headspace" is the distance between the face of the breech and the base of the cartridge when the action is closed, and excessive headspace can be dangerous as well as impair accuracy. For instance, unsupported brass fired in a rifle action with excessive headspace can rupture, allowing gas to blow rearward like a rocket exhaust. Because your safety is on the line, Forster Headspace Gages are made with painstaking care and exacting manufacturing standards to ensure accurate testing of your rifle's chamber. If a rifle closes on a GO gage, the rifle chamber will accept any ammunition that is made within S.A.A.M.I. (industry standard) specifications. If a rifle closes on a NO GO gage, the rifle chamber might have excessive headspace. Most gunsmiths chamber a rifle's headspace between the GO and NO GO dimensions. If a rifle closes on a FIELD gage, the rifle chamber is dangerously close to or already over the S.A.A.M.I. specified maximum chamber size.

This set is for: 243,308,7mm-08

postcontent:
Up for grabs is nice  9mm specs below.  
This pistol is a licensed reproduction of the Beretta 92, and comes in a variety of finishes with a variety of grip styles.
Like the Beretta, the Taurus PT92 utilizes the open-slide design where the upper portion of the slide is cut away exposing much of the barrel itself. The original PT92 was exactly like the original Beretta 92, though it was also unusual for the time in that it featured a squared trigger guard for supporting the index finger of the opposite hand while firing, a feature which was subsequently introduced to the Beretta 92 with the 92SB-F (92F) model in 1985. The Taurus PT92 is less expensive than the Beretta 92 in most cases.

title: For Sale:  Vintage SILVA Ranger 15T Compass and case - like new!
location: White Bear Lake, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
Here's a classic vintage Silva compass, the model 15T Ranger and it is like new!
The Silva 15T is the benchmark that compasses are compared against and is one of the best you can buy. It has a red lanyard with a screwdriver to adjust declination, a cover with a sighting mirror (for shooting an azimuth or for signalling) and a base with three rubber feet and two measuring scales for use with a map.

This one is an older model with all aluminum construction and the longer plastic plate....no scratches....like new! The users manual is dated 4-70 so this classic is about 43 years old now and is in perfect shape.
With new all-plastic Silva's going for 50 bucks without the leather case, this one is a real bargain. When these are available they usually fetch prices up to a hundred bucks WITHOUT the leather case!

The leather cases are over 12 bucks new alone....but as I said, this compass has a longer base so this case doesn't snap shut....but still protects it's contents.

Complete with original instructions, this beautiful compass can be yours for 50 bucks cash.
Thanks for looking!
